						<p><strong>My story</strong></p>
						<p>After studying Music at University I returned home to the west country to work in health and social care as a senior support worker, and specifically I worked with adults with Autism. I loved this job! It meant I could help others to pursue their interests and work alongside them to problem solve on a daily basis with the aim to support great people to live their best lives. Many of my clients loved video games and computing, and one day I stumbled upon a treasure trove of online computing courses that I had great fun introducing to my clients. What I didnt expect was that when I sat down to support my clients complete these courses, I would discover a passion for coding that I never knew was in me!</p>
